com.emc.ecs.tool

Class BucketWipeOperations

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.emc.ecs.tool.BucketWipeOperations

  • public class BucketWipeOperations
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides multiple Asynchronous operations for deleting objects from buckets

    An instance of the class can be used multiple times for different buckets as long as the S3Client configuration remains the same.

    Operations are async, users should pass in an instance of BucketWipeResult into which the result of the bucket wipe operation (number of objects deleted etc) will be placed. The operation is complete when the BucketWipeResult.getCompletedFuture() completes.

    MaxConcurrent controls how many concurrent delete actions can be submitted at once, this allows an instance to handle deletion of millions of objects from a bucket without causing a runaway OOM condition. Note that the maxConcurrent applies to ALL actions within an instance, for example if there are two callers they will both be competing to add new delete actions within the maxConcurrent limit.

                            int numThreads,

        Create an instance of the BucketWipeOperations class. Instances are thread safe and can be used by multiple callers simultaneously
        Parameters:
        client - The pre-configured S3 client to use when contacting the S3 server
        numThreads - Number of threads to use in the thread pool for simultaneous actions
        maxConcurrent - Total number of actions to be queued up at once. New delete actions will be blocked until there is "space" in the queue
